Stardict Client
==============

A simple, suckless Stardict dictionary lookup client written in pure C.

Features:
- Reads Stardict .ifo, .idx, and .dict files
- Performs binary search for fast word lookup
- Outputs definition to stdout
- Supports prefix queries to list words
- Minimal dependencies (only standard C libraries)

Usage:
    ./dict-sl <dict_dir> <dict_name> <mode> <query>
    ./dict-sl <mode> <query>  # uses defaults from config.h

Where mode is:
    --query or -q: list words starting with <query> prefix
    --word or -w: lookup exact <query> word

Example:
    ./dict-sl --word hello
    ./dict-sl langdao-ec-gb langdao-ec-gb --query hel

Compilation:
    make

Notes:
- Assumes 32-bit offsets in .idx file (ignores idxoffsetbits)
- Does not handle compressed .idx.gz or .dict.dz files
- Ignores sametypesequence for simplicity
- Definitions are assumed to be plain text
